-- PE firm ECI Partners raises 500 mln stg for tenth buyout fund
-- By Esha Vaish in Bangalore
-- Thu Sep 04, 2014 05:53AM EDT
-- None



Sept 4 (Reuters) - British private equity firm ECI Partners said it raised 500 million pounds ($823 million) for its tenth buyout fund, mainly from existing institutional investors.

The PE firm had planned to raise 400 million pounds when it launched the fundraising in April. (http://bit.ly/1rNWzgq) ECI Partners has now raised over 1.6 billion pounds of external capital since it was launched in 1976.  ECI 10, as the new fund is known, will focus on making buyouts with an enterprise value of between 10 million pounds to 150 million pounds, the company said.